 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Dawn, and he is still raking,\" Genemon says to the dark, as if the dark had asked.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 2
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Morning at the board. The hands take their rice at the threshold; the steward's papers hold the table's far end — an estate's worth of paper on a kitchen table. Genemon calls you up from the step without looking up.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Two hands took the lowland road this week. Wages drawn through the day they left, lines struck. The yard is short. The work is not.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "It is the first you have heard of any leaving.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Terms. Work, sun to sun, at what the yard wants doing — hired by the day, counted in the book. Meals at the threshold, morning and evening. The woodshed corner and a mat. No coin: the house's coin is spoken for before it reaches the yard. Objections are heard now or kept. The paddies want you by full light.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Nobody stops eating. Two hands lost was a morning's talk; one stray kept is not even that. The bowls go on.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The board has heard it. That serves for witness.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "He opens the day-book to a page already half-filled with other men.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "On the veranda above the step, Naoyuki has stopped — the second son, papers of his own under one arm. Passing, and made a witness like the rest of the room.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The house is glad of —\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Naoyuki"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The sentence stops. He stands with it a moment, as if he has read it back and found it not worth the ink.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Two hands left. You were here. That is all it is.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Naoyuki"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "He goes on along the veranda. He looked at you once.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Then Genemon takes up the brush, and asks it plainly, at board volume. The room hears without listening.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"One thing before the ink. If a claim follows you here, I enter it against your board. Is anything owing on you?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"And if there were?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Then the house's claim comes first, while you eat its rice. After that — whoever can find you. So far nobody has asked.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You begin to mark the turning of the days, and the four seasons with them.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Rank ↑ — The day-hand 日雇",
   "count": 1
  }
